Full Description: Green Arrow Capital Management, LLC, founded in 2007, is an investment manager investing primarily in the North American capital markets. The firm employs multiple portfolio managers with specialized expertise in particular sectors, industry groups, or financial products. Portfolio managers are generally making investments based on detailed fundamental analysis of the industry, company, or products. Within their particular specializations, the managers and their teams of analysts determine the optimal mix of instruments on a relative value basis, aiming to maximize return while minimizing direct market exposure and controlling risk. Using this approach, the firm seeks superior risk-adjusted returns while minimizing correlation to the overall market or specific investment sectors. The firm has in place risk management processes to achieve portfolio diversification with defined parameters for each portfolio manager. Our primary investment strategy is Relative Value Fundamental Equity. The firm operates offices in New York, Greenwich, and Dallas, and is a Millennium group company.

Full Description: We are Ardor. We're specialists in direct marketing and sales and our passion is the renewable energy sector. We are a small privately held firm based in Cincinnati that is rapidly growing, thanks to our dedicated staff and awesome clients. If there's one thing that all businesses have in common, it's the need for loyal customers. This also happens to be one of the most challenging feats for companies large and small. This is why multi-million dollar corporations are turning to Ardor. We are experts in generating revenue by bringing in new customers and thereby increasing market share. Human to human, face to face interaction is at the core of Ardor's methods. There is nothing in the world that can replace a smile and a handshake. Rather than a "sell, sell, sell" approach, Ardor believes in establishing a genuine rapport and first building trust. Our account managers spend time building relationships with our clients' customers and finding out their pain points. From there, they propose custom solutions. In most cases, our clients have spent millions of dollars building brand recognition. They've advertised through billboards, commercials, online ads, print ads, and everything in between. Indirect marketing, however, has its limits. While it can do wonders to turn a brand into a household name, it doesn't necessarily compel consumers to go out and buy. Ardor bridges this gap by driving sales today. We are a team unlike most. We proudly work with some of the most impressive professionals in the U.S. They are highly passionate and goal-driven individuals of sound character who will stop at nothing to achieve success. Ardor cultivates these existing qualities by providing opportunities for our team members to grow and develop. Training is a standard part of our weekly routines. Backed by the support of Ardor's management team, all employees are encouraged to step out of their comfort zones and take on new responsibility. We offer ample opportunity for advancement and live by a philosophy that hard work should be rewarded. The direct result is that our clients receive 100% from Ardor. We can be counted on to deliver - and we will do so with ardor. See what's happening today at Ardor by visiting us on instagram @WeAreArdor or going to this link: https://www.instagram.com/weareardor/

Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: MotivateU is an Enterprise SaaS corporation that uses artificial intelligence to provide patent-pending synchronization software and data-driven dashboards from any mobile device. Our solution is targeted at the fitness market and fills the gap between the human-driven traditional gyms and data-driven AI fitness, allowing gym owners, fitness instructors, and members to enjoy the benefits of both worlds. We use AI to enhance fitness instructors, not to replace them, because we believe it's time to put community back into community-based fitness. With 9 out of 10 Americans planning to continue to work-out from home traditional fitness is getting left behind with pen & pencil or low-tech band-aids while AI fitness is removing the human element altogether. But humans crave social connections with other humans - in fact, it's the greatest predictor of longevity. Our user interviews confirm the importance of community with 53% of people who exercise and 91% of trainers reporting that they enjoy the aspect of community and interaction with others.  Our easily accessible, mobile solution does not require any hardware and allows fitness instructors to provide real-time, motivating feedback during remote, or hybrid, interactive classes, without having to stop demonstrating proper form and technique while saving countless hours on data analysis through AI generated insights and customized, actionable wellness plans. For fitness users instead of working out in front of a mirror, you can work out in front of a live fitness instructor - the same instructor you have at your local gym - while still receiving the data-driven metrics that are expected from AI fitness.

Founder Donnette Thomas provides adults with the tools they need to pave a pathway to success in their personal and professional life. Mindful Missions of SC works with individuals on the opposite end of the age spectrum and their families. Mindful Missions of SC will enable a variety of therapeutic and enrichment services to be offered to vulnerable youth. Services are designed to aid children affected by situations that encompass abuse, drug and alcohol addiction, family dysfunction, and violence.

Description: Dacentec is a provider of dedicated hosting, co-location, and green cloud data center services.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Dacentec`s mission is to design, build & operate world greenest cloud datacenters and to help partners to build their own green cloud datacenters. Dacentec brings the energy usage below what is traditionally needed, by investing in both the supply side and load side of the datacenter. Dacentec believes datacenters need to change their behavior in order to survive in the fast evolving datacenter market: - Start measuring the power (load side) in detail for every piece of equipment and this in time; - Shut down non used equipment; - Put the less important equipment at a lower power state; - Optimize airflow in datacenters and avoid overcooling, redefine rack layouts to optimize air cooling - Optimise the density without impacting the airflow or energy needs per square meter - Look more into the choice of equipment that is placed inside the datacenter, since that choice has a significant impact on the power usage

Description: JAXUSA focuses on recruiting new companies and expanding their existing business community.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: JAXUSA Partnership, the private, nonprofit division of the JAX Chamber, is the economic development initiative overseeing efforts in the seven-county Northeast Florida region Their mission is to be a catalyst for economic growth and maximize the region’s unique resources to aggressively recruit jobs and capital investment to their area. Since 1990, they have been a driving economic force within Northeast Florida and, together with their partners, have helped create more than 100,000 jobs and $6 billion in capital investment. Using strategic research and targeted marketing, JAXUSA focuses on recruiting new companies and expanding their existing business community. They offer a variety of services for businesses that are considering corporate relocation or expansion in Jacksonville and Northeast Florida. Their dedicated project management team assists company executives and site consultants in all aspects of the site selection process. Economic development partners in Baker, Clay, Duval, Flagler, Nassau, Putnam and St. Johns comprise the strong partnership that drives the business development process forward. They work closely with the independent authorities – JAXPORT, JAA, JEA and JTA – to build infrastructure to ensure they have a sustainable business climate to offer companies. Talent is an integral part of the process, and their partnerships with CareerSource Northeast Florida and local colleges and universities help develop and attract a steady stream of skilled workers.
